  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6757.44 sitting above the 6750 max negative gamma wall (-11.9B) but below the 6775 positive gamma flip (+7.6B), dealers are currently in forced buying mode as they hedge short gamma positions. The massive negative GEX concentration between 6745-6755 creates a dangerous amplification zone where any downside move will trigger aggressive dealer selling, while a push above 6775 shifts dealers into selling mode to hedge long gamma positions. The gex_surge event combined with extreme 1-min/5-min changes (28.5%/82.6%) signals violent dealer rebalancing is already underway.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect explosive moves in either direction with 6750 as the make-or-break level for continued upside momentum.",
